messages.message: currently we don't have a great way to segregate what is available for UDFs and what is just part of our internal code
we need to make that distinction clearer, but currently people use things a little bit ad-hoc, like the ParseIBOCR object, which now has essentially entered the public user domain
what is the specific use-case where you need to make the code available?
For the report app, I basically have a few typed dicts that I want people to use to build the format for the report app
It's just a format check at the moment so not too important to have, but would be nice to have if supported
